[[全球化|全球化]]，即信息、货物、资本和人员跨越政治和地理边界的流动，使传染病在世界范围内迅速传播，同时也使饥饿和贫困等因素得到缓解，这些因素是全球健康的关键决定因素<ref name= global>{{cite web |author=Daulaire, N. |title=Globalization and Health |date=July 12, 1999 |work=International RoundtabResponses to Globalization: Rethinking Equity and Health’ jointly organized by the Society for International Development (SID), the World Health Organization (WHO), and The Rockefeller Foundation (RF) |url=http://www.globalhealth.org/assets/html/drmed3.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110622194117/http://www.globalhealth.org/assets/html/drmed3.html|archive-date=2011-06-22}} <!-- same as doi:10.1057/palgrave.development.1110077 ? -->
</ref>。历史上，疾病在广泛地理范围内的传播有所增加。

在当今全球化时代，世界比以往任何时候都更加相互依存。 高效而廉价的交通使几乎没有地方无法到达，全球农产品贸易的增加使越来越多的人接触到动物疾病，这些疾病随后跨越了物种障碍（见[[人畜共通傳染病|人畜共通傳染病]]）<ref name= Well >{{Cite web |url=http://www.richardwellsresearch.com/richardwells/pdfs%20and%20documents/BJIC%20Oct |title=Archived copy |access-date=2006-12-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928202437/http://www.richardwellsresearch.com/richardwells/pdfs%20and%20documents/BJIC%20Oct |archive-date=2007-09-28 |url-status=dead }}</ref>。

